bulkDeposit(address,uint256,uint256,addr.details: Does NOT support native deposits.Callable by SOLVER_ROLE.

refundDeposit(uint256,address,address,ui.details: Once a deposit share lock period has passed, it can no longer be reverted.It is possible the admin does not setup the BoringVault to call the transfer hook,      but this contract can still be saving share lock state. In the event this happens      deposits are still refundable if the user has not transferred their shares.      But there is no guarantee that the user has not transferred their shares.Callable by STRATEGIST_MULTISIG_ROLE.

setShareLockPeriod(uint64).details: This not only locks shares to the user address, but also serves as the pending deposit period, where deposits can be reverted.If a new shorter share lock period is set, users with pending share locks could make a new deposit to receive 1 wei shares,      and have their shares unlock sooner than their original deposit allows. This state would allow for the user deposit to be refunded,      but only if they have not transferred their shares out of there wallet. This is an accepted limitation, and should be known when decreasing      the share lock period.Callable by OWNER_ROLE.

updateAssetData(address,bool,bool,uint16.details: The accountant must also support pricing this asset, else the `deposit` call will revert.Callable by OWNER_ROLE.

accountant().notice: The AccountantWithRateProviders this contract is working with.

allowAll(address).notice: Allow a user to transfer or receive shares.

allowFrom(address).notice: Allow a user to transfer shares.

allowOperator(address).notice: Allow an operator to transfer shares.

allowTo(address).notice: Allow a user to receive shares.

beforeTransfer(address,address,address).notice: Implement beforeTransfer hook to check if shares are locked, or if `from`, `to`, or `operator` are on the deny list.If share lock period is set to zero, then users will be able to mint and transfer in the same tx.         if this behavior is not desired then a share lock period of >=1 should be used.

bulkDeposit(address,uint256,uint256,addr.notice: Allows on ramp role to deposit into this contract.

bulkWithdraw(address,uint256,uint256,add.notice: Allows off ramp role to withdraw from this contract.

denyAll(address).notice: Deny a user from transferring or receiving shares.

denyFrom(address).notice: Deny a user from transferring shares.

denyOperator(address).notice: Deny an operator from transferring shares.

denyTo(address).notice: Deny a user from receiving shares.

deposit(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Allows users to deposit into the BoringVault, if this contract is not paused.

depositNonce().notice: The deposit nonce used to map to a deposit hash.

depositWithPermit(address,uint256,uint25.notice: Allows users to deposit into BoringVault using permit.

fromDenyList(address).notice: Mapping `from` address to a bool to deny them from transferring shares.

isPaused().notice: Used to pause calls to `deposit` and `depositWithPermit`.

operatorDenyList(address).notice: Mapping `opeartor` address to a bool to deny them from calling `transfer` or `transferFrom`.

pause().notice: Pause this contract, which prevents future calls to `deposit` and `depositWithPermit`.

refundDeposit(uint256,address,address,ui.notice: Allows DEPOSIT_REFUNDER_ROLE to revert a pending deposit.

shareLockPeriod().notice: After deposits, shares are locked to the msg.sender's address         for `shareLockPeriod`.

shareUnlockTime(address).notice: Maps user address to the time their shares will be unlocked.

toDenyList(address).notice: Mapping `to` address to a bool to deny them from receiving shares.

unpause().notice: Unpause this contract, which allows future calls to `deposit` and `depositWithPermit`.

updateAssetData(address,bool,bool,uint16.notice: Updates the asset data for a given asset.

vault().notice: The BoringVault this contract is working with.
